y:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">How do you assure yourself that the recorded crime figures for your area are correct?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 54pt; text-indent:-18pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">•</span><span style="font:7.0pt 'Times New Roman'">&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0;&#xa0; </span><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">To what extent can you trust the crime statistics for your area?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">Taking each in turn:</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt; font-weight:bold">What, if any, targets do you set for your police force?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">The </span><a href="http://www.leics.pcc.police.uk/Document-Library/Planning-and-Money/Police-and-Crime-Plan/Executive-Summary---WEB.pdf"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt; text-decoration:underline">Police and Crime Plan 2013-2017 Executive Summary</span></a><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt"> lists the targets that have been set for the 2013/14 Financial Year.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt; font-weight:bold">What impact do you think this has on police recording crime practices?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">The setting of targets has no impact on police recording crime practices in Leicestershire, HMIC have reaffirmed this in their most recent inspections of Crime Recording Standards in the Force area.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt; font-weight:bold">How do you assure yourself that the recorded crime figures for your area are correct?</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">The key reassurances are:</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#54555b; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10.5pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.3pt; padding-left:6.7pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">Leicestershire Police have a dedicated in house audit team that as a core function undertake detailed audits across the broad spectrum of police action to ensure that the Force's crime recording practices meet the correct recording requirements under the national recording standards. </span></li><li style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:10.5pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.3pt; padding-left:6.7pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#2a2a2a; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt">Regular 1-1 meetings with the Chief Constable to discuss performance around targets with an emphasis on ethical recording and culture.</span></li><li style="color:#292929; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Recent inspections by the HMIC concluded that "Leicestershire Constabulary almost always records crimes accurately as required by the crime recording standards" Review of Police Crime and Incident Report Jan 2012.</span></li><li style="color:#292929; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">HMIC: As part of the national HMIC review of crime and incident data integrity Leicestershire</span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">will be inspected in Jan 2014</span></li><li style="color:#292929; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Crime Registrar is in place to ensure recording accuracy</span></li><li style="color:#292929; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">The Crime and Incident Recording Standards, which provide the framework for consistency in recording.</span></li><li style="color:#292929; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Recently, Leicestershire Police invited HMIC's national crime recording lead and the national</span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">crime registrar to the Force to provide on-going training </span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">I </span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">briefing around good crime recording practices to a wide range of managers to ensure local practices and procedures are of the highest level.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:10.5pt; font-weight:bold">To what extent can you trust the crime statistics for your area?</span></p><ul type="circle" style="margin:0pt; padding-left:0pt"><li style="color:#292929; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Previous HMIC inspections have judged that crime is being appropriately recorded in Leicestershire.</span></li><li style="color:#292929; font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Leicestershire Police have a monthly meeting chaired by the ACC Crime or Ch Supt Head of Crime where senior managers and auditors convene to look and review crime recording practices and compliance procedures</span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></li><li style="font-family:'Courier New'; font-size:11pt; margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 29.6pt; padding-left:6.4pt; text-indent:0pt"><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Additionally, I have made it very clear to the Chief Constable that I will hold him personally accountable for the accuracy and integrity of the Force's recording of crime statistics; he knows that, should either an internal or external audit find evidence of purposeful </span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">mis</span><span style="color:#292929; font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">-recording on any substantial scale, I will immediately reconsider his suitability to continue in that appointment.</span></li></ul><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Times New Roman'; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div></body></html>